# Day 2 – Java Control Statements

Control statements are used to control the flow of execution in a Java program.

## Types of Control Statements

1. Decision Making Statements
   - if
   - if-else
   - switch

2. Looping Statements
   - for loop
   - while loop
   - do-while loop

3. Jump Statements
   - break
   - continue
   - return

## If Statement
The if statement is used to execute a block of code only if a condition is true.

## Switch Statement
The switch statement is used when multiple conditions depend on a single variable.

## Loops
Loops are used to execute a block of code repeatedly until a condition becomes false.
